{
  "texts": [
    "strongly NP-hard if it remains NP-hard when all of its input parameters are bounded by a polynomial in the length of the input, 4. strongly NP-complete if it remains NP-complete when all of its input parameters are bounded by a polynomial in the length of the input, 5.",
    "APX-hard if there exists a PTAS reduction from every problem in APX to this problem, 6.",
    "APX-complete if the problem is APX-hard and in APX.",
    "NP-hard problems cannot be solved in polynomial time.",
    "However, some NP-hard problems can be approximated in polynomial time-be it up to some constant approximation ratio (APX) or up to any approximation ratio (PTAS, FPTAS)."
  ]
}